	<h1>Youth Advisory Board Toolkit</h1>
		

<p>Youth with mental health, emotional or behavioral needs can promote positive change when they are engaged in  leadership opportunities that give them a chance to express their experiences and perspectives.  A Youth Advisory Board can help youth develop self-advocacy skills and promote individual as well as team leadership to promote effective systems of care and support.</p>
<p>This Youth Advisory Board Toolkit is a prototype to help your organization or group benefit from the youth voice.  The purpose of a youth board is to promote an authentic way for youth to engage with meaning.</p>
<p>The toolkit covers the following areas:</p>
<ul>
<li>Information about PACER&rsquo;s Youth Advisory Board on Mental Health</li>
<li>How to set up a Youth Advisory Board</li>
<li>Sample Forms</li>
</ul>
